# Raw Data Documentation

This folder contains the raw data used in the project.

1. petrol_prices_raw.csv  
   - Source: FuelIO (Melbourne fuel price history)
   - Coverage: January 2022- March 2026
   - Geographic Coverage: Melbourne
   - Variable: Average petrol price
   - Unit: Cents per litre
   - Fuel type: Unleaded 
   - Date accessed: 23/3/26
   - Method: Monthly average petrol prices manually extracted from the FuelIO app.
   - Reason: FuelIO does not provide a downloadable dataset, so manual extraction was required.
   - Limitation: 

2. vic_transport_patronage_raw.xlsx  
   - Source: Transport Patronage | vic.gov.au
   - Source link:https://discover.data.vic.gov.au/dataset/monthly-public-transport-patronage-by-mode
   - Coverage: January 2018- January 2026
   - Georgaphic Coverage: Melbourne Metropolitan 
   - Variables: Year, Month, Metropolitan Train, Metropolitan Tram, Metropolitan Bus, Regional Train, Regional Coach, Regional Bus.
   - File format: csv
   - Date accessed: 23/3/26
   - Contains monthly public transport usage for trains, trams, and buses.
   - Downloaded directly from the Victorian Government website.

3. monthly_public_holidays.csv
   - Source: https://business.vic.gov.au/business-information/public-holidays/victorian-public-holidays-2025
   - Transcribed into an excel for appropriate years and converted into a csv. 
   - Coverage: January 2022- December 2025
   - Date accessed: 30/3/26
   - Geographical location: Victoria
   - Unit: Public holidays per month. 
   - Method: Holidays per month manually extracted
   - Reason: vic.gov does not provide a downloadable dataset, so manual extraction was required.

4. melbourne_rainfall_raw.csv
- Source: Bureau of Meteorology (BoM) – Monthly Rainfall (Station 086338, Melbourne Olympic Park)
- Source link: https://reg.bom.gov.au/jsp/ncc/cdio/weatherData/av?p_nccObsCode=139&p_display_type=dataFile&p_stn_num=086338
- Coverage: 2013–2026
- Geographic Coverage: Melbourne, Victoria
- Variables: Year, Jan–Dec monthly rainfall (mm), Annual rainfall (mm)
- File format: csv
- Date accessed: 30/3/26
- Contains monthly rainfall totals derived from daily observations.
- Downloaded directly from the BoM Climate Data Online portal.

5. melbourne_population_change.csv
population_quarterly_raw.csv
- Source: Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) – National, state and territory population
- Source link: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/people/population/national-state-and-territory-population
- Coverage: Quarterly, 2021–2025
- Geographic Coverage: Victoria
- Variables: Quarter, Total population change, Natural increase, Net overseas migration
- File format: csv
- Date accessed: 30/3/26
- Notes:
    • ABS only publishes population estimates on a quarterly basis.
    • Monthly population data does not exist for Australia.
    • This dataset is therefore included in quarterly form as raw data.
    • In the cleaning script, quarterly values are converted to monthly using standard step interpolation (repeating the quarterly value for each month in the quarter) so that the final merged dataset is monthly.
- Downloaded directly from the ABS website.

All raw data is stored exactly as obtained, with no cleaning or modification.
